====================================================================================================
Metadata Configuration Fragment
====================================================================================================
	
SUMMARY:
	Provides centralized configuration management for AI models, API routing,
	and system behavior across the Unified AI Gateway Sample. Acts as the single source of truth for
	model definitions, backend pool mappings, API type specifications,
	and cache settings. Essential foundation fragment for all gateway operations.

INPUT VARIABLES:
	- None (this is the base foundational configuration fragment)
	
OUTPUT VARIABLES:
	- metadata-config: String - Complete JSON configuration containing all model, auth, and routing settings
	
DOWNSTREAM CONSUMERS:
	- central-cache-manager fragment: Processes and caches the configuration for performance optimization
	- backend-selector fragment: Uses models and api-types sections for routing decisions and backend selection
	- token-limiter fragment: Uses models configuration for tier lookup and LLM token throttling
	- diagnostic-headers fragment: References model and API information for debug response headers
	
UPSTREAM DEPENDENCIES:
